[Crim. No. 3241. In Bank. May 15, 1929.] In the Matter of the Application of C. C. MERRILL for a Writ of Habeas Corpus.

Robert B. Murphey and Hunsaker, Britt & Cosgrove for Petitioner.

U. S. Webb, Attorney-General, and Charles A. Wetmore, Deputy Attorney-General, for Respondent.

THE COURT.

Upon the authority of the Matter of Application of Battelle for Writ of Habeas Corpus, filed May 14, 1929, ante, p. 227 [277 Pac. 725], the order for commitment herein is vacated and the petitioner discharged..
